1
00:00:02,878 --> 00:00:05,005
[grunting]

2
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:10,052
[thwacking]

3
00:00:22,105 --> 00:00:23,273
What a dummy.

4
00:00:24,525 --> 00:00:27,069
[exhaling]

5
00:00:29,071 --> 00:00:31,323
Oh, Master.

6
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:34,618
[Nagakura]
At it again, training so early?

7
00:00:36,078 --> 00:00:38,580
My apologies.
Did I wake you?

8
00:00:38,664 --> 00:00:39,748
Nah.

9
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:46,088
Don't overdo it.
Your hands are all torn up.

10
00:00:47,798 --> 00:00:49,091
[sighs]

11
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,302
[Sasaki] Master.
[Nagakura] Hm?

12
00:00:52,386 --> 00:00:54,179
I'm sorry to impose, but...

13
00:00:58,016 --> 00:01:00,435
I'd be grateful
for your instruction.

14
00:01:03,063 --> 00:01:05,107
What are you talking about?

15
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:07,150
You're plenty strong already.

16
00:01:07,234 --> 00:01:09,027
There's nothing more
I can teach you.

17
00:01:09,111 --> 00:01:10,028
[exclaims softly]

18
00:01:10,112 --> 00:01:13,240
[♪♪♪]

19
00:01:13,323 --> 00:01:17,119
You're the only master I'll
ever have, Nagakura Shinpachi.

20
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:19,079
Cut it out.
Spare me the flattery.

21
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:21,248
It's not flattery.

22
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:23,542
You accepted your own
lack of natural talent

23
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:26,420
and overcame it with nothing
but pure hard work.

24
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:28,672
The way you became
this strong...

25
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:30,841
you're my inspiration, Master.

26
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:32,259
[scoffs]

27
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:35,512
No talent, no talent...
You've got some nerve.

28
00:01:35,554 --> 00:01:37,681
I can't tell
if you're complimenting me

29
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:39,515
or insulting me.

30
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,726
My apologies.

31
00:01:42,185 --> 00:01:45,229
Whatever.
It's the truth, anyway.

32
00:01:51,445 --> 00:01:52,404
[grunts]

33
00:01:55,574 --> 00:01:58,035
You've gotten good
at that disarming technique.

34
00:01:58,076 --> 00:01:59,661
All thanks to you, Master.

35
00:02:06,043 --> 00:02:07,169
Bring it.

36
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:10,922
This "talentless" senior
will give you a lesson.

37
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:13,508
Thank you very much.

38
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:23,518
[insects chirring]

39
00:02:39,242 --> 00:02:42,245
Half past six. I'll be
waiting at Shinkenji Temple.

40
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,254
Guess who?

41
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:52,881
[sword slices]
[blood spilling]

42
00:02:58,762 --> 00:03:00,347
[grunts]

43
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:06,687
[coughs]

44
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,774
THE CORPS CODE

45
00:03:10,816 --> 00:03:12,442
[yelling]

46
00:03:12,526 --> 00:03:15,278
[grunting]
[blows landing]

47
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:26,289
[coughs]

48
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:28,375
Come on, Shimada.
What's the matter?

49
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:32,003
Put more spirit into it.

50
00:03:32,087 --> 00:03:35,340
[gasping]
My apologies, Vice-Commander.

51
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:39,010
[Okita]
Hijikata doesn't hold back.

52
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:42,514
[Kondo]
Face every opponent
with everything you've got.

53
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:45,767
It's the only way to show
true respect for your opponent.

54
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,608
[grunting]

55
00:03:53,692 --> 00:03:56,236
[♪♪♪]

56
00:03:59,156 --> 00:04:00,657
[groans]

57
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:03,952
[groaning]

58
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:15,797
[Okita]
But they are all intimidated.

59
00:04:15,881 --> 00:04:17,673
[student 1]
He's just too damn strong.

60
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:20,260
[student 2]
He's making Shimada
look like a child...

61
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:23,764
Out of the way!

62
00:04:23,847 --> 00:04:25,390
[Hijikata]
Heisuke, we're practicing.

63
00:04:25,474 --> 00:04:28,894
This is no time for that!

64
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:34,274
Aijiro...
Aijiro has been killed!

65
00:04:40,197 --> 00:04:42,365
[indistinct chatter]

66
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:44,451
[doshin]
Back off.

67
00:04:45,368 --> 00:04:47,245
Back off. Come on.

68
00:04:47,329 --> 00:04:50,457
[♪♪♪]

69
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:51,457
Hey!

70
00:04:56,755 --> 00:04:58,590
[crowd exclaiming]

71
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:17,609
SONG OF THE SAMURAI

72
00:05:25,116 --> 00:05:26,701
Are you sure it was Aijiro?

73
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:29,621
Yes.

74
00:05:31,373 --> 00:05:32,749
According to
the magistrate's office,

75
00:05:32,832 --> 00:05:34,543
the body had countless
sword wounds.

76
00:05:35,919 --> 00:05:37,254
They said the fatal wound

77
00:05:37,295 --> 00:05:39,548
was being run through
from back to stomach.

78
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:44,511
Does Shinpachi know?

79
00:05:47,806 --> 00:05:48,723
No idea.

80
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:53,478
Haven't seen Nagakura
at the dojo today.

81
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:56,940
Any idea who did it?

82
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,608
No idea.

83
00:05:58,650 --> 00:06:02,404
The magistrate's office thinks
it was probably a robber

84
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:04,281
since his belongings were taken.

85
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:06,283
A robber?

86
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:08,702
No way he'd be killed
by a common thief.

87
00:06:10,579 --> 00:06:13,081
[footsteps approaching]

88
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:16,626
[Niimi]
Coming in.

89
00:06:20,505 --> 00:06:22,507
What do you want, Niimi?

90
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,720
I hear one of your men
got himself killed.

91
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:30,432
I see you get news quickly.

92
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:33,810
Our faction's full of new blood,
you see.

93
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:37,647
Can't have them losing morale
over something trivial.

94
00:06:39,107 --> 00:06:40,567
Trivial?

95
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:43,528
The way he died.

96
00:06:45,238 --> 00:06:46,489
Get it right.

97
00:06:48,325 --> 00:06:49,743
His name was Sasaki Aijiro.

98
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:51,119
Ah?

99
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,495
There is no one in this corps

100
00:06:52,537 --> 00:06:54,289
named "the guy who got killed."

101
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:57,626
[scoffs]
Killed by a common thief,
I hear.

102
00:06:59,169 --> 00:07:02,464
A weakling like that isn't even
worth learning the name of.

103
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:04,174
You bastard...

104
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,718
How dare you insult
a fallen comrade?

105
00:07:06,801 --> 00:07:08,470
One...

106
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:11,056
If you fail to kill
and take a wound to your back,

107
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:12,432
it is seppuku.

108
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:20,190
This Sasaki...
whatever his name was...

109
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:23,443
was cut down
while turning his back.

110
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:28,657
He'd have had to commit seppuku
even if he had survived.

111
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:33,078
That's the Corps Code, isn't it?

112
00:07:34,913 --> 00:07:36,623
Kondo.

113
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:41,294
One of your men has disgraced
the name of the Mibu Roshigumi.

114
00:07:41,378 --> 00:07:43,880
How are you going to answer
for this?

115
00:07:43,922 --> 00:07:45,382
Hey, Niimi.

116
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:46,716
[Nagakura]
Stop, Toshi.

117
00:07:48,343 --> 00:07:49,469
Shinpachi.

118
00:07:51,096 --> 00:07:53,014
What he's saying is bullshit.

119
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:56,351
There's no way Aijiro
would turn his back

120
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:57,602
on some common thief.

121
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:05,944
In that case...
who do you claim did it?

122
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:10,740
I don't know,
but I'll find whoever it is.

123
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:13,785
I'll find the bastard...

124
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:16,997
and finish them.

125
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:38,518
THE CORPS CODE

126
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:41,520
ONE, IF YOU FAIL TO KILL
AND TAKE A WOUND TO YOUR BACK,

127
00:08:41,604 --> 00:08:42,938
IT IS SEPPUKU

128
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:48,653
[sighs]

129
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:06,212
[screams]

130
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:17,223
[footsteps approaching]

131
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:19,726
[Seiki]
What's up? Bye.

132
00:09:42,123 --> 00:09:45,043
[♪♪♪]

133
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:56,054
Couldn't resist
causing some trouble, huh?

134
00:09:57,514 --> 00:09:59,182
You think I overdid it?

135
00:10:00,892 --> 00:10:05,313
There's nothing like picking
on the weak, is there?

136
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:08,108
I just get so into it.
Ha-ha!

137
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:09,234
Whatever.

138
00:10:10,527 --> 00:10:11,569
[coin clinks]

139
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:14,030
Whoa, damn.

140
00:10:14,072 --> 00:10:17,117
Are you sure I should get
this much for that little thing?

141
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:22,288
But are you sure about this?

142
00:10:23,915 --> 00:10:26,709
The truth is, I was ordered
to assassinate Kondo Isami

143
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:28,753
so I went undercover with them.

144
00:10:28,837 --> 00:10:30,922
That's not your place
to worry about.

145
00:10:32,549 --> 00:10:33,800
Right.

146
00:10:36,427 --> 00:10:38,263
So, what's next?

147
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:41,099
You've done enough.

148
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:42,350
[laughing]

149
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:44,018
For real?

150
00:10:44,102 --> 00:10:47,230
You think taking out one grunt
is enough to bring down Kondo?

151
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,023
Ah.

152
00:10:51,234 --> 00:10:54,154
You're a true strategist, Niimi.
Just what I'd expect.

153
00:10:55,488 --> 00:10:59,075
Guess I'll use this cash
to celebrate.

154
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:00,118
Surely.

155
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:04,289
You didn't mess up?

156
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:06,791
Of course not.

157
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:22,765
You were listening,
weren't you, Yamazaki?

158
00:11:25,059 --> 00:11:31,399
Money, money, money!
Money! Money!

159
00:11:31,482 --> 00:11:33,443
Keep an eye on him.

160
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:34,444
Yes.

161
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,877
Move.

162
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,878
Welcome.

163
00:11:53,087 --> 00:11:54,005
Hey.

164
00:11:56,090 --> 00:12:00,678
Skipping patrol to go drinking?
Must be nice.

165
00:12:00,762 --> 00:12:04,766
Crap. I got busted.
[chuckles]

166
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:06,392
And you're not even wearing
your damn coat.

167
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:10,647
You're not taking this
seriously?

168
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:13,691
[laughs]
No, no, no, of course I am!

169
00:12:13,775 --> 00:12:16,527
Nagakura, you came
all the way out here...

170
00:12:16,611 --> 00:12:18,363
So aren't you slacking off too?

171
00:12:20,031 --> 00:12:22,200
Won't you have a drink with me?

172
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:24,869
Forget that. Saeki...

173
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:28,498
It's about Aijiro.

174
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:31,125
[laughing]

175
00:12:31,209 --> 00:12:33,878
Heard he got killed
by some thugs, right?

176
00:12:37,715 --> 00:12:38,675
Here.

177
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:41,010
[chuckles]
Thanks.

178
00:12:43,388 --> 00:12:44,931
I saw his body.

179
00:12:46,808 --> 00:12:51,062
The fatal blow
one strike from back to stomach.

180
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:55,400
The style of the sword strike
was Shindo Munen-ryu.

181
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:58,528
That's your style too, isn't it?

182
00:12:58,569 --> 00:13:00,280
[drink continues pouring]

183
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:03,908
What's more, you're from Choshu.

184
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:13,293
What a waste!

185
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:19,257
You're the one
who killed Aijiro.

186
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:26,222
[laughing]
Whoa, what is this
all of a sudden?

187
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:29,434
Why would I go and kill
one of our own comrades?

188
00:13:29,517 --> 00:13:31,894
Besides, there must be
a thousand swordsmen in Kyo

189
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:33,354
who use that style.

190
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:36,733
Including you, right, Nagakura?

191
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:39,027
Anyway, I already deserted
the Choshu clan.

192
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,739
What happened to your finger?

193
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:44,449
Ah... Ha-ha.

194
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:49,078
A girl bit me over
in the pleasure district.

195
00:13:49,162 --> 00:13:51,914
You'd wear a splint for just
a little bite on your pinky?

196
00:13:53,665 --> 00:13:56,836
Aijiro broke it with his
disarming technique, didn't he?

197
00:14:00,757 --> 00:14:01,883
Don't move.

198
00:14:06,888 --> 00:14:08,890
You plan to fight
with that hand?

199
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,190
[sighing]
Ah...

200
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,404
[laughing]

201
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:26,866
[♪♪♪]

202
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:38,127
[grunting]

203
00:14:38,169 --> 00:14:40,171
[laughing]

204
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:54,977
Aah!
Oh-ho-ho-ho!

205
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:02,110
[laughing]

206
00:15:05,321 --> 00:15:08,032
Even you could see
the huge gap between us, right?

207
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:10,952
You know...

208
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:14,163
you're going to get crushed,
so why aren't you running?

209
00:15:15,498 --> 00:15:19,627
So, master and student
are alike, huh? Hilarious.

210
00:15:21,504 --> 00:15:24,757
Let me ask you instead.

211
00:15:24,841 --> 00:15:26,134
Huh?

212
00:15:28,386 --> 00:15:30,263
There's one thing
I just don't get.

213
00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:37,270
Why did you have to kill Aijiro
in such a brutal way?

214
00:15:39,564 --> 00:15:41,065
A man with your skill...

215
00:15:42,984 --> 00:15:45,528
you could have finished him off
in a single blow.

216
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:48,197
[laughing]

217
00:15:48,281 --> 00:15:51,367
I guess a hack like you
wouldn't get it.

218
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:55,997
Killing someone
in a crushing win....

219
00:15:58,415 --> 00:16:01,210
feels better
than screwing a woman.

220
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:02,879
[laughing]

221
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:05,214
You bastard!

222
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,265
[gasps playfully]

223
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:17,977
What the hell is that?

224
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,729
Trying to make me die
of laughter?

225
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:21,439
[laughing]

226
00:16:28,696 --> 00:16:30,448
Don't you mock me!

227
00:16:33,493 --> 00:16:35,077
[yelling fiercely]

228
00:16:43,461 --> 00:16:46,214
And there it is.
A decisive victory.

229
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:52,220
Now this feels good.

230
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:57,308
Way too easy.

231
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:02,146
[grunting]

232
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:09,194
I can't hold it in anymore.

233
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:18,246
Sorry, but here I come!

234
00:17:25,502 --> 00:17:26,628
[exclaims]

235
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:30,675
[flesh squelches]
[chokes]

236
00:17:34,262 --> 00:17:36,514
You know, Saeki...

237
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:38,516
the real thrill comes...

238
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:46,232
when you crush someone
far beyond your own skill.

239
00:17:49,026 --> 00:17:50,444
[coughing]

240
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:55,533
W-Wait! Nagakura, please!

241
00:17:57,368 --> 00:18:00,955
Do you have any proof that
I'm the one who killed Aijiro?

242
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:02,540
Y-You don't have any, do you?

243
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:04,709
I'm not sloppy
with things like that.

244
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:08,004
I-If you finish me off now

245
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:09,797
the truth about me
being the killer

246
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,299
will just be swept
under the rug.

247
00:18:11,382 --> 00:18:14,343
S-S-So, look! I'll cooperate!

248
00:18:14,385 --> 00:18:16,721
I'll go to the magistrate's
office... anywhere you say.

249
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:20,474
[crying]

250
00:18:20,558 --> 00:18:24,103
I'll tell you everything I know,
I swear.

251
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:33,654
Please! Just spare my life!

252
00:18:42,413 --> 00:18:43,331
I see.

253
00:18:44,874 --> 00:18:45,791
Fine.

254
00:18:49,253 --> 00:18:50,463
[sniveling]
Thank you!

255
00:18:51,339 --> 00:18:54,634
Thank you so much.

256
00:18:56,052 --> 00:18:59,263
I'll be in your debt
for the rest of my life.

257
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:04,518
[blade rings]

258
00:19:05,603 --> 00:19:06,520
Oh?

259
00:19:07,563 --> 00:19:08,564
[blade clatters]

260
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:13,736
You're such a transparent
piece of shit.

261
00:19:13,778 --> 00:19:16,447
[gasping]

262
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:19,617
[neck snaps]

263
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:34,298
[♪♪♪]

264
00:19:52,942 --> 00:19:54,735
[Niimi]
So, Nagakura made his move.

265
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:57,405
[Yamazaki]
Yes.

266
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,366
Just as I predicted.

267
00:20:02,118 --> 00:20:03,369
The winner is...

268
00:20:05,246 --> 00:20:06,664
Nagakura Shinpachi.

269
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:10,334
I see.

270
00:20:11,961 --> 00:20:14,422
Saeki was a fool.

271
00:20:14,463 --> 00:20:19,343
For all his talent with a sword,
he let his skill go to his head.

272
00:20:22,555 --> 00:20:24,598
[chuckles]

273
00:20:24,682 --> 00:20:29,145
And with this...
Kondo Isami is finished.

274
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:33,357
[♪♪♪]

275
00:20:48,706 --> 00:20:50,583
There are no sword wounds
on him.

276
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:54,378
Unbelievable...

277
00:20:55,629 --> 00:20:58,424
Nagakura...
You beat the best dual-wielder

278
00:20:58,507 --> 00:21:00,092
with just brute force.

279
00:21:00,176 --> 00:21:05,264
Hey. Hey, Shinpachi! Hey, why?

280
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:08,517
Why'd you try to shoulder this
all alone?

281
00:21:08,559 --> 00:21:12,021
Toshi, what's the problem?

282
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:15,107
You guys, that scumbag Saeki
is the one who killed Aijiro!

283
00:21:15,191 --> 00:21:17,401
This was righteous revenge!
Right?!

284
00:21:18,652 --> 00:21:19,612
Answer me!

285
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:23,949
If only there were proof
of that.

286
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:42,468
Kondo, any luck?

287
00:21:42,551 --> 00:21:45,387
I searched Saeki's belongings

288
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:49,225
but found no proof
that he killed Sasaki Aijiro.

289
00:21:49,308 --> 00:21:51,477
Hey!
Did you check properly, boss?

290
00:21:52,728 --> 00:21:53,646
Yes.

291
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,398
Nagakura...

292
00:21:57,650 --> 00:21:59,652
why did you pass judgment
on Saeki?

293
00:22:01,612 --> 00:22:03,614
If you passed judgment
on an assumption

294
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:06,242
then this is
just a private duel

295
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:08,911
fought for your own
selfish reasons.

296
00:22:08,953 --> 00:22:13,040
Don't tell me
you've forgotten the Corps Code?

297
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:16,001
One.

298
00:22:16,085 --> 00:22:18,754
Do not engage
in personal fights.

299
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:21,757
Anyone who violates these
articles must commit seppuku.

300
00:22:26,512 --> 00:22:27,888
I am prepared for that.

301
00:22:32,852 --> 00:22:36,939
[♪♪♪]

302
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:40,150
Hold on a second!
What do you mean, prepared?!

303
00:22:42,987 --> 00:22:43,946
Hey, Shinpachi!

304
00:22:46,782 --> 00:22:48,492
How did you know
it was Saeki?

305
00:22:50,369 --> 00:22:51,787
At least answer that much.

306
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:56,625
Everyone...

307
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:01,380
I'm sorry
for all the trouble.

308
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:05,551
Hey, Shinpachi...

309
00:23:07,261 --> 00:23:08,637
But I have no regrets.

310
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:21,817
Knock it off!

311
00:23:26,572 --> 00:23:30,701
[♪♪♪]

312
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:42,254
Farewell.

313
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:43,547
Shinpachi!

314
00:23:44,882 --> 00:23:46,133
[wakizashi clatters]

315
00:23:49,303 --> 00:23:50,638
Shinpachi.

316
00:23:52,723 --> 00:23:55,684
You're not meant to fall
in a place like this.

317
00:24:00,314 --> 00:24:01,440
Boss...

318
00:24:19,375 --> 00:24:20,542
Niimi!

319
00:24:22,836 --> 00:24:27,591
I ask that you grant a brief
stay of Shinpachi's seppuku.

320
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:31,345
[Okita]
Kondo, please stop!

321
00:24:31,428 --> 00:24:32,471
I beg of you!

322
00:24:32,554 --> 00:24:34,014
[Hijikata]
Hey!

323
00:24:35,265 --> 00:24:36,725
[Niimi]
Oh?

324
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:40,479
So, the Commander himself
would bend the Corps Code.

325
00:24:41,772 --> 00:24:44,024
And you expect to maintain
discipline that way?

326
00:24:46,819 --> 00:24:50,698
Shinpachi's failure is my own.

327
00:24:55,285 --> 00:24:56,620
In his place...

328
00:24:58,497 --> 00:25:00,416
I will resign my position
as Commander.

329
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:03,002
What are you saying,
boss!

330
00:25:03,085 --> 00:25:04,128
As will I.

331
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:12,386
I shall resign my post
as vice-commander.

332
00:25:12,469 --> 00:25:14,430
Yamanami...

333
00:25:14,471 --> 00:25:16,724
[laughing heartily]

334
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:20,853
What is this farce?!

335
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:24,982
As if that could ever be a fair
trade for Nagakura's seppuku.

336
00:25:25,065 --> 00:25:28,944
Then Nagakura's life
must be pretty damn cheap.

337
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:31,321
Then...

338
00:25:35,075 --> 00:25:36,118
what do we need to do?

339
00:25:38,245 --> 00:25:39,246
Commit seppuku.

340
00:25:40,330 --> 00:25:42,332
Hey, you bastard! Cut it out!

341
00:25:42,416 --> 00:25:44,168
Who's being ridiculous here?

342
00:25:44,251 --> 00:25:48,172
Anyone who violates the Corps
Codes must commit seppuku!

343
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:52,051
You're the ones
who made that rule!

344
00:25:53,761 --> 00:25:55,971
[Serizawa exclaiming slowly]

345
00:25:58,682 --> 00:26:00,726
This is a lively bunch.

346
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:06,815
Niimi, come on,
cut them some slack.

347
00:26:06,857 --> 00:26:08,525
But...

348
00:26:08,609 --> 00:26:12,237
Besides, what's fun
in making them commit seppuku?

349
00:26:13,363 --> 00:26:14,823
[stammers]

350
00:26:22,706 --> 00:26:24,917
Kondo. Yamanami!

351
00:26:26,668 --> 00:26:28,921
You have Serizawa's mercy
to thank for this.

352
00:26:32,966 --> 00:26:36,553
Hey, Niimi. Watch your mouth.

353
00:26:36,637 --> 00:26:38,514
Why would
a Vice-Commander like me

354
00:26:38,597 --> 00:26:40,516
listen to
a rank-and-file soldier?

355
00:26:40,557 --> 00:26:42,226
You rotten country-samurai!

356
00:26:42,309 --> 00:26:46,855
From this moment on,
you're all just common soldiers.

357
00:26:46,939 --> 00:26:50,526
You will all serve
under Serizawa.

358
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:52,653
That is the condition
for granting Nagakura

359
00:26:52,736 --> 00:26:54,029
a reprieve from seppuku.

360
00:26:55,697 --> 00:26:58,033
Is that acceptable, Serizawa?

361
00:27:00,661 --> 00:27:03,914
I don't care.
Do whatever you want.

362
00:27:20,764 --> 00:27:22,558
[shouts]
[punch thuds]

363
00:27:22,641 --> 00:27:24,101
What the hell are you doing!

364
00:27:30,691 --> 00:27:31,984
Yamanami, you too!

365
00:27:37,573 --> 00:27:40,409
[Niimi]
That was a surprise.

366
00:27:40,450 --> 00:27:42,536
I can't believe
you showed them mercy.

367
00:27:42,619 --> 00:27:44,246
[Serizawa]
Mercy, huh.

368
00:27:44,329 --> 00:27:47,583
[Niimi]
It was the best chance
to take out Kondo, wasn't it?

369
00:27:47,624 --> 00:27:50,794
I don't remember
showing any mercy.

370
00:27:51,795 --> 00:27:54,131
Eh?
Niimi...

371
00:27:55,883 --> 00:27:58,635
If you want to kill,
do it with your own hands.

372
00:27:58,719 --> 00:28:01,096
Seppuku is the most boring thing
in this world.

373
00:28:01,180 --> 00:28:02,806
[yawns]

374
00:28:03,724 --> 00:28:04,850
Serizawa!

375
00:28:07,311 --> 00:28:08,353
I heard the news.

376
00:28:09,646 --> 00:28:11,106
I heard you used the Corps Code

377
00:28:11,190 --> 00:28:12,941
to bring the Kondo faction
under our control.

378
00:28:12,983 --> 00:28:15,819
[chuckles]
That was all Niimi's doing.

379
00:28:17,696 --> 00:28:22,159
Well, well.
I'm impressed, Vice-Commander.

380
00:28:22,242 --> 00:28:24,578
Watch your mouth!

381
00:28:24,661 --> 00:28:26,663
I'm your superior officer.

382
00:28:26,747 --> 00:28:29,291
What example does that set
for our men?

383
00:28:29,374 --> 00:28:32,711
[scoffs]
That's ridiculous.
We're on the same side.

384
00:28:35,672 --> 00:28:38,091
Well, how about we go out

385
00:28:38,175 --> 00:28:40,636
and celebrate bringing the Kondo
faction under our wing?

386
00:28:40,677 --> 00:28:41,887
No.

387
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:46,141
I think it's about time
for our little festival.

388
00:28:46,225 --> 00:28:48,393
[laughs]

389
00:28:48,477 --> 00:28:50,729
[♪♪♪]

390
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:57,903
SEPTEMBER 24, 1863

391
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,305
[Hirayama]
We are the Mibu Roshigumi!

392
00:29:25,347 --> 00:29:27,724
[stammering]
Hey, hey, hey!
What's all this about?

393
00:29:27,808 --> 00:29:30,852
[whimpering]

394
00:29:30,894 --> 00:29:33,730
This is an official inspection.

395
00:29:33,814 --> 00:29:35,649
You've cornered the market
on raw silk

396
00:29:35,732 --> 00:29:37,609
and kept all the profits
for yourselves!

397
00:29:37,693 --> 00:29:40,654
It's time you learned
how much suffering

398
00:29:40,737 --> 00:29:43,573
you've caused
the people of this city!

399
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:45,909
Move out of the way.

400
00:29:49,579 --> 00:29:53,041
This money isn't for you
to line your own pockets with.

401
00:29:53,125 --> 00:29:55,252
It will be used
for the people of Kyo.

402
00:29:56,753 --> 00:29:57,754
Got it?

403
00:29:57,838 --> 00:29:59,464
[men whimpering]

404
00:29:59,548 --> 00:30:01,383
We'll be back.

405
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:03,343
All right, let's move out.

406
00:30:03,427 --> 00:30:04,428
[soldiers]
Sir!

407
00:30:13,854 --> 00:30:15,981
Now... let's begin.

408
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:25,907
[laughs]

409
00:30:25,991 --> 00:30:27,617
What are you doing,
Serizawa?

410
00:30:27,701 --> 00:30:29,453
Isn't it obvious?
It's a festival!

411
00:30:29,536 --> 00:30:32,622
Come on, you light one, too.

412
00:30:34,750 --> 00:30:36,084
Do it.

413
00:30:36,126 --> 00:30:38,754
Sir! Bring the fire, you lot!

414
00:30:38,837 --> 00:30:41,590
[men shouting indistinctly]

415
00:30:53,810 --> 00:30:57,356
You need more fire!
Go on! Keep going!

416
00:30:57,439 --> 00:30:58,982
[laughs]

417
00:30:59,066 --> 00:31:00,859
Burn it! Burn more!

418
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:11,870
Serizawa! We're losing
our source of money!

419
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:13,372
Look, Niimi.

420
00:31:16,166 --> 00:31:20,379
It just burns.
That's the beauty of it.

421
00:31:20,462 --> 00:31:24,132
[♪♪♪]

422
00:31:24,174 --> 00:31:26,009
For everything to burn...

423
00:31:27,928 --> 00:31:29,638
and turn to ashes.

424
00:32:02,379 --> 00:32:04,339
[laughing]

425
00:32:04,423 --> 00:32:08,552
Serizawa Kamo.
A man I must have.

426
00:32:10,345 --> 00:32:12,180
A moral compass
that points somewhere

427
00:32:12,222 --> 00:32:14,099
beyond good and evil,
profit and loss.

428
00:32:14,182 --> 00:32:17,602
One who has no interest
in money or honor...

429
00:32:17,686 --> 00:32:19,938
is a fascinating man indeed.

430
00:32:21,106 --> 00:32:24,860
Whether or not Serizawa Kamo
sides with us

431
00:32:24,901 --> 00:32:26,736
rests entirely
on your shoulders, Mr. Niimi.

432
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:29,030
You needn't worry, Mr. Kusaka.

433
00:32:29,114 --> 00:32:32,033
He's just a simple-minded brute.

434
00:32:32,075 --> 00:32:35,245
He doesn't have a shred
of loyalty to the Shogunate.

435
00:32:36,580 --> 00:32:38,081
I'm counting on you.

436
00:32:39,124 --> 00:32:42,169
Our preparations
are all set as well.

437
00:32:42,252 --> 00:32:44,087
[Sanjo]
On this occasion...

438
00:32:44,171 --> 00:32:45,881
[Kusaka]
The day after your men attack

439
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:47,257
and burn down the Yamato-ya...

440
00:32:48,550 --> 00:32:53,388
The Emperor has announced
he'll lead

441
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:56,766
the expulsionist faction
in seizing power.

442
00:32:56,850 --> 00:32:58,894
So the signal
to overthrow the shogunate

443
00:32:58,935 --> 00:33:00,061
has finally been given.

444
00:33:00,145 --> 00:33:01,897
We must use this momentum

445
00:33:01,938 --> 00:33:07,652
to eliminate
Matsudaira Katamori!

446
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:12,407
I'm counting on you, Niimi.

447
00:33:12,491 --> 00:33:15,076
How you drove Kondo Isami
into a corner

448
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:17,913
the other day
was truly brilliant.

449
00:33:17,954 --> 00:33:21,166
I'll take care of Lord Katamori.

450
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:24,336
150 Men in the Serizawa faction
are under my direct command.

451
00:33:25,587 --> 00:33:28,131
I can mobilize them
at a moment's notice.

452
00:33:28,965 --> 00:33:30,759
That's very reassuring.

453
00:33:38,183 --> 00:33:40,477
This is for you, Niimi.
Do as you like.

454
00:33:59,079 --> 00:34:03,500
[♪♪♪]

455
00:34:10,549 --> 00:34:12,425
[footsteps]

456
00:34:22,101 --> 00:34:26,188
[panting excitedly]

457
00:34:26,273 --> 00:34:30,068
Money. Money. Money! Money!

458
00:34:31,027 --> 00:34:32,612
You really love money that much?

459
00:34:32,654 --> 00:34:36,199
I do. It's the one thing
that will never betray me.

460
00:34:43,831 --> 00:34:44,873
Found it.

461
00:35:04,436 --> 00:35:08,231
Good, things
are really coming together!

462
00:35:10,066 --> 00:35:12,569
Oume, how about a song?

463
00:35:13,862 --> 00:35:15,113
Certainly.

464
00:35:21,411 --> 00:35:26,249
[Oume playing and singing]

465
00:35:34,049 --> 00:35:36,926
[playing and singing fade]

466
00:35:42,932 --> 00:35:44,059
Serizawa.

467
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:48,188
[♪♪♪]

468
00:35:48,271 --> 00:35:49,439
What's this?

469
00:35:57,864 --> 00:35:59,908
[loud shouting]

470
00:35:59,949 --> 00:36:03,411
[Todo, chuckling]
You are so loud.
Come on! Bring it on!

471
00:36:22,972 --> 00:36:25,392
[laughs]

472
00:36:27,977 --> 00:36:29,938
Hey, Shimada!

473
00:36:29,979 --> 00:36:32,691
How many times
do I have to tell you?

474
00:36:32,774 --> 00:36:36,611
Don't you have any damn respect
for your seniors?!

475
00:36:36,695 --> 00:36:41,157
My apologies. I'll be sure
to go easy on you next time.

476
00:36:41,241 --> 00:36:42,325
Are you mocking me?!

477
00:36:42,409 --> 00:36:45,328
Hey, you are getting
all worked up.

478
00:36:46,162 --> 00:36:47,455
I mean...

479
00:36:47,539 --> 00:36:49,290
Yeah, I can see
why you're pissed.

480
00:36:49,374 --> 00:36:51,584
You two are the only ones
even training.

481
00:36:54,254 --> 00:36:56,756
Everyone's been sucked
into the Serizawa faction

482
00:36:58,508 --> 00:37:01,136
and now it's just us left
in the Kondo faction.

483
00:37:01,177 --> 00:37:04,514
And the boss gets demoted
to a regular grunt.

484
00:37:06,015 --> 00:37:08,518
This is beyond pathetic!

485
00:37:13,106 --> 00:37:14,566
He's still Kondo,

486
00:37:14,649 --> 00:37:16,526
whether he's the Commander
or not.

487
00:37:19,112 --> 00:37:20,238
I'm sorry.

488
00:37:21,990 --> 00:37:23,533
Don't get all worked up, Soji.

489
00:37:24,284 --> 00:37:25,493
It's not like you.

490
00:37:28,413 --> 00:37:32,625
Besides, I don't exactly hate
that it's just us now.

491
00:37:32,709 --> 00:37:35,503
It's like being
back in the Shieikan dojo.

492
00:37:37,088 --> 00:37:38,506
[sighs]

493
00:37:44,220 --> 00:37:46,014
[Shimada]
One more round, please.

494
00:37:46,055 --> 00:37:48,475
No! I don't want to anymore!

495
00:38:03,239 --> 00:38:05,408
You didn't eat again?

496
00:38:13,750 --> 00:38:16,669
[♪♪♪]

497
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:23,760
[sighs]

498
00:38:32,393 --> 00:38:34,479
[Kondo]
Shinpachi's not eating?

499
00:38:45,198 --> 00:38:48,535
The boss even got on his hands
and knees to save his life.

500
00:38:50,411 --> 00:38:53,414
Does he even understand that?

501
00:38:53,498 --> 00:38:55,375
Now, now, don't be
so hard on him.

502
00:38:56,334 --> 00:38:57,794
If I can save all of you

503
00:38:59,295 --> 00:39:02,465
by bowing my head to the ground

504
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,802
then I'll gladly grovel
in the dirt all day long.

505
00:39:07,345 --> 00:39:08,596
Cut the noble act.

506
00:39:11,307 --> 00:39:13,977
That might be fine for you

507
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:17,146
but when our commander,
Kondo Isami, bows his head

508
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:20,525
it's the same as making
all of us grovel on the ground.

509
00:39:22,986 --> 00:39:24,445
I'm sorry, Toshi.

510
00:39:25,655 --> 00:39:26,656
But...

511
00:39:28,283 --> 00:39:29,826
I feel for Shinpachi.

512
00:39:33,288 --> 00:39:34,789
He couldn't protect Aijiro.

513
00:39:36,666 --> 00:39:39,669
I feel like
he's punishing himself for it.

514
00:39:39,752 --> 00:39:43,089
But we can't
just let this go on!

515
00:39:48,428 --> 00:39:49,888
Hey, Yamanami.

516
00:39:51,472 --> 00:39:53,099
Can't you do
something?!

517
00:39:55,018 --> 00:39:56,769
I'm at
my breaking point.

518
00:39:56,853 --> 00:39:57,770
Hijikata.

519
00:40:02,358 --> 00:40:03,943
I feel the same way.

520
00:40:08,364 --> 00:40:11,492
[shuffling footsteps
approaching]

521
00:40:16,372 --> 00:40:17,498
[Hijikata]
Kanbei.

522
00:40:22,712 --> 00:40:24,547
I need to have a word with you.

523
00:40:25,673 --> 00:40:27,800
[indistinct shouting]

524
00:40:33,723 --> 00:40:35,725
As fired up as ever, I see.

525
00:40:37,060 --> 00:40:38,895
Hijikata. Haven't you heard?

526
00:40:40,188 --> 00:40:41,522
An imperial edict is out.

527
00:40:41,606 --> 00:40:44,067
The Emperor will personally
expel the foreigners.

528
00:40:45,234 --> 00:40:46,194
An imperial edict?

529
00:40:47,779 --> 00:40:49,530
[Yamanami]
Does that mean
that the Imperial Court

530
00:40:49,572 --> 00:40:51,449
is moving to overthrow
the shogunate?

531
00:40:53,034 --> 00:40:55,787
[Hijikata]
So that's why you're all
so on edge.

532
00:40:55,870 --> 00:40:58,748
[Sagawa]
That would plunge Kyo
into chaos once more.

533
00:40:58,831 --> 00:41:02,210
Now, more than ever,
we need the Mibu Roshigumi.

534
00:41:02,293 --> 00:41:06,422
But for a matter
of such importance...

535
00:41:06,506 --> 00:41:08,424
Serizawa
is our head commander.

536
00:41:08,508 --> 00:41:09,884
Head commander!

537
00:41:11,094 --> 00:41:14,097
This man, Serizawa...
is he truly up to the task?

538
00:41:15,974 --> 00:41:19,185
He extorts "donations"
from everyone...

539
00:41:19,268 --> 00:41:20,603
and I hear he even burned down

540
00:41:20,687 --> 00:41:22,563
a silk wholesaler's shop
recently.

541
00:41:25,608 --> 00:41:30,738
Kondo! Yamanami! Hijikata!
What's the matter with you!

542
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:33,282
He extorts "donations"
from everyone.

543
00:41:33,366 --> 00:41:34,409
Pathetic! Utterly pathetic!

544
00:41:34,492 --> 00:41:35,535
You think I don't know that?!

545
00:41:35,618 --> 00:41:36,911
Don't get cocky with me!

546
00:41:39,998 --> 00:41:42,166
Where has
your samurai spirit gone?

547
00:41:45,503 --> 00:41:47,463
If you let him run wild,

548
00:41:47,547 --> 00:41:50,258
you'll bring shame
on Lord Katamori.

549
00:41:50,341 --> 00:41:53,219
[Matsudaira]
I don't give a damn
about my reputation

550
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:54,220
My lord!

551
00:42:00,226 --> 00:42:02,103
Don't you dare hold back!

552
00:42:02,145 --> 00:42:03,271
[all]
Sir!

553
00:42:03,354 --> 00:42:04,397
Let's practice!

554
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:06,441
[all shouting]

555
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:07,775
Kanbei.

556
00:42:07,817 --> 00:42:09,277
Yes, sir!

557
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:15,283
I couldn't care less about the
Mibu-Roshi's internal squabbles.

558
00:42:15,324 --> 00:42:16,534
However...

559
00:42:16,617 --> 00:42:17,869
the edict
about the Emperor himself

560
00:42:17,952 --> 00:42:19,287
leading the overthrow
of the shogunate.

561
00:42:21,539 --> 00:42:23,291
It's a forgery.

562
00:42:23,332 --> 00:42:24,876
[Sagawa]
A forgery?

563
00:42:27,170 --> 00:42:31,966
Choshu plans to use
a forged edict to win allies

564
00:42:33,009 --> 00:42:35,762
and pick a fight
with the shogunate.

565
00:42:38,222 --> 00:42:39,474
Those bastards... playing dirty.

566
00:42:39,557 --> 00:42:41,559
Playing dirty?
There's no such thing.

567
00:42:43,561 --> 00:42:45,146
This is war.

568
00:42:54,781 --> 00:42:56,949
[Serizawa clears throat]

569
00:42:57,033 --> 00:42:58,242
Serizawa!

570
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:02,330
Well now,
sorry to crash the party.

571
00:43:02,413 --> 00:43:04,457
[Aizu retainer]
Hey! You're in the lord's
presence! Stand back!

572
00:43:04,540 --> 00:43:05,750
Move.

573
00:43:07,668 --> 00:43:11,172
Hey, hey,
what the hell's going on?

574
00:43:11,255 --> 00:43:13,382
I'm just saying I have something
to tell the boss.

575
00:43:13,466 --> 00:43:16,344
And you're the ones making
all this damn noise, aren't you?

576
00:43:16,385 --> 00:43:17,804
Huh? What's the deal?

577
00:43:17,887 --> 00:43:19,138
[Matsudaira]
Kamo!

578
00:43:21,057 --> 00:43:22,892
What is it you wanted
to discuss?

579
00:43:24,352 --> 00:43:27,522
Ah... Our very own Niimi
is connected with Choshu.

580
00:43:27,605 --> 00:43:31,818
[♪♪♪]

581
00:43:31,901 --> 00:43:33,611
You bastard!
What the hell are you saying?!

582
00:43:33,694 --> 00:43:36,072
I found this
in Niimi's letterbox.

583
00:43:43,871 --> 00:43:46,916
It's a letter from Kusaka Genzui
of Choshu, addressed to Niimi.

584
00:43:46,999 --> 00:43:48,960
[Serizawa]
It's all written right there.

585
00:43:49,043 --> 00:43:53,047
Saeki Matasaburo is a Choshu
assassin, hired by Niimi.

586
00:43:53,089 --> 00:43:55,758
Saeki is an assassin?
[Serizawa] Yes.

587
00:43:56,634 --> 00:43:57,760
Then...

588
00:44:00,263 --> 00:44:01,430
The whole thing with Aijiro...

589
00:44:01,514 --> 00:44:03,266
Niimi and Choshu
were behind that, too.

590
00:44:07,270 --> 00:44:08,521
Originally, Kondo...

591
00:44:08,604 --> 00:44:09,772
KONDO

592
00:44:10,898 --> 00:44:13,276
...it seems the plan was
to get rid of you.

593
00:44:16,904 --> 00:44:19,740
Ah, right, and by the way...

594
00:44:19,824 --> 00:44:24,787
Niimi killed Abiru Eisaburo too.

595
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:29,917
So it's revenge for Abiru.

596
00:44:34,672 --> 00:44:35,798
[Matsudaira]
So?

597
00:44:38,926 --> 00:44:41,804
What are you going to do
about Niimi?

598
00:44:41,888 --> 00:44:43,222
Mm... Not a damn thing.

599
00:44:43,306 --> 00:44:45,391
I knew all along
and didn't do anything.

600
00:44:46,976 --> 00:44:49,270
The man's been far too useful
to me.

601
00:44:49,353 --> 00:44:53,566
If that's true, then you're
subject to punishment as well.

602
00:44:53,649 --> 00:44:54,650
I don't care.

603
00:44:54,734 --> 00:44:56,277
My Lord...

604
00:44:56,319 --> 00:44:59,322
This isn't just an internal
squabble between Mibu factions.

605
00:44:59,405 --> 00:45:03,618
I won't let this man
get away with this. Serizawa!

606
00:45:03,659 --> 00:45:04,994
Yeah, yeah, whatever.

607
00:45:05,077 --> 00:45:06,996
I'll cut you down
right here and now.

608
00:45:10,291 --> 00:45:14,795
Yes! Finally took the bait.

609
00:45:14,879 --> 00:45:19,592
Hey Sagawa, don't chicken out
like last time.

610
00:45:19,675 --> 00:45:23,179
[♪♪♪]

611
00:45:24,263 --> 00:45:25,514
Oh...

612
00:45:27,183 --> 00:45:31,354
If you wanna kill me, you better
come at me with all you've got.

613
00:45:33,231 --> 00:45:34,148
Hey, hey.

614
00:45:34,232 --> 00:45:35,650
[Sagawa]
What do you think you're doing?

615
00:45:35,691 --> 00:45:37,276
[chuckles]

616
00:45:38,736 --> 00:45:41,989
Sorry. This one's my fight.

617
00:45:42,031 --> 00:45:44,867
Oh? Gotten a little stronger,
have we?

618
00:45:47,870 --> 00:45:49,455
[both chuckle]

619
00:45:51,540 --> 00:45:55,878
[Yoshiaki Dewa's "Chiruran
Shinsengumi Requiem" playing]
